review_blob: Well the fact the last time i was drinking this i was stood in their brewery and it was free, might mean ive rated this slightly higher than perhaps i would otherwise. But it does have two things going for it: First - E&S; dont seem able to brew a bad beer - this is another fine addition to the range, this one with a slightly fruity flavour and second, its named after my home town and a little local pride never hurts now does it?
